@hugenberg
on-arrival: dnvp_relation -= 8
face-image: img/portraits/JoosJoseph.jpg

Following Hugenberg's letter to Westarp in 1927 critisizing the DNVP's participation in government, him and his allies in the Pan German League have worked to fill the DNVP's provincial organsations with their supporters. Using the outrage generated by inflammatory Lambach article as a pretext to attack the national leadership, they have managed to discredit the National Conservative wing of the party, leading to the election of Alfred Hugenberg as chairman by a slim margin.
With the support of the party's national organisation, it is expected that Hugenberg will turn the DNVP from a party based on agrarian and conservative values into an instrument of the radical right. Westarp will continue to stay on as the chairman of the DNVP's Reichstag delegation and work to prevent a secession of the Christian Socials and Young Conservatives.


@compromise
